We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The location of the mass, which is in the anal canal proximal to the pectinate line suggests that it is an anal squamous cell carcinoma. The most likely lymph node involvement is the internal iliac lymph nodes due to the anatomic drainage. The inferior mesenteric lymph nodes drain the descending colon and sigmoid colon, while the external iliac lymph nodes drain the lower limb and the pelvic wall. The deep inguinal lymph nodes drain the superficial tissues of the lower limb.
